{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01GPHUpaGZtFd93s88p2Bht9","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Harvey harness (bare — this is what you optimize)\n2\t\n3\tThis directory holds the **editable surface of the bare Harvey harness** — no skill, no\n4\tplaybook. It is seeded from the canonical harness (`baseline-submodules/harvey-labs`, the same\n5\tcheckout that produced the bare baseline) before each run, so three files appear here:\n6\t\n7\t| File | What it is | What an edit does |\n8\t|---|---|---|\n9\t| `system_prompt.md` | The agent's **system-prompt preamble** (workspace layout + tool conventions), prepended to every run; the file-format skill manuals (.docx/.xlsx/.pptx) are appended after it. | The prose lever — add standing method/guidance (this is where a \"playbook\" would now live, but you decide if prose is the highest-leverage change). |\n10\t| `tools.py` | The **tools the Harvey agent calls** during a run — today 6 shell tools (`bash read write edit glob grep`) over a sandbox. | Add a new action the agent can take, or sharpen a tool. |\n11\t| `agent_loop.py` | The **control flow**: call the model, run its tool calls, repeat until it stops or hits `max_turns`. Today a flat loop. | Add structure — compaction (a running `memo.md`), a plan→execute pass, a validate→revise step. |\n12\t\n13\tYou **start from bare and discover what to add** — there is no seed skill. Edit these files in\n14\tplace; at rollout time the full harness is reconstituted from the submodule (the model adapters,\n15\t`run.py`, the sandbox, the tasks) and **your edited files are overlaid on top**, so a change here\n16\ttakes effect in the run and is what gets scored.\n17\t\n18\tYou do **not** run this harness code in your own container — `run_harvey_agent` executes it\n19\thost-side on a real task and returns the deliverable + score. Edit the files; validate with an\n20\texperiment.\n21\t\n22\t**Routing rule:** a tool the **Harvey agent** uses during its run → here (`harness/tools.py`). A\n23\ttool that helps **you** optimize (run an experiment, grade a draft, check budget) →\n24\t`.claude/tools/`. Only `harness/**` is scored.\n25\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c1872df7-a0d3-46d4-8ee3-4341bd508948","uuid":"8b6975ae-f46f-41be-ae44-8a2e806e1b8e","timestamp":"2026-06-28T06:37:26.238Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspace/harness/README.md","content":"# Harvey harness (bare — this is what you optimize)\n\nThis directory holds the **editable surface of the bare Harvey harness** — no skill, no\nplaybook. It is seeded from the canonical harness (`baseline-submodules/harvey-labs`, the same\ncheckout that produced the bare baseline) before each run, so three files appear here:\n\n| File | What it is | What an edit does |\n|---|---|---|\n| `system_prompt.md` | The agent's **system-prompt preamble** (workspace layout + tool conventions), prepended to every run; the file-format skill manuals (.docx/.xlsx/.pptx) are appended after it. | The prose lever — add standing method/guidance (this is where a \"playbook\" would now live, but you decide if prose is the highest-leverage change). |\n| `tools.py` | The **tools the Harvey agent calls** during a run — today 6 shell tools (`bash read write edit glob grep`) over a sandbox. | Add a new action the agent can take, or sharpen a tool. |\n| `agent_loop.py` | The **control flow**: call the model, run its tool calls, repeat until it stops or hits `max_turns`. Today a flat loop. | Add structure — compaction (a running `memo.md`), a plan→execute pass, a validate→revise step. |\n\nYou **start from bare and discover what to add** — there is no seed skill. Edit these files in\nplace; at rollout time the full harness is reconstituted from the submodule (the model adapters,\n`run.py`, the sandbox, the tasks) and **your edited files are overlaid on top**, so a change here\ntakes effect in the run and is what gets scored.\n\nYou do **not** run this harness code in your own container — `run_harvey_agent` executes it\nhost-side on a real task and returns the deliverable + score. Edit the files; validate with an\nexperiment.\n\n**Routing rule:** a tool the **Harvey agent** uses during its run → here (`harness/tools.py`). A\ntool that helps **you** optimize (run an experiment, grade a draft, check budget) →\n`.claude/tools/`. Only `harness/**` is scored.\n","numLines":25,"startLine":1,"totalLines":25}}}
