{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_015DYd12Xsianq4szJJQsYuQ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Budget is healthy ($90 metered cap, untouched). I now have a clear diagnosis:\n\n**The cost structure:** `input_tokens` = Σ over turns of the full re-sent context. The agent reads all big docs in the first ~6 turns, then spends 15–110 turns drafting via `bash`/`write` (tiny tool results) while **re-carrying every raw document on every one of those turns**. That resident raw-doc bulk, multiplied across drafting turns, is where millions of tokens go.\n\n**The mechanism:** in `agent_loop.py`, evict large, *aged* raw tool outputs (read/bash) from the carried context — replacing each with a compact **re-read handle** stub — while keeping a generous recent window full. The agent read each doc in full (accuracy preserved at read time); it just stops re-carrying the bytes once they've aged out, and can re-read on demand. Let me first build my analysis tool (compounds), then the edit."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":160,"cache_creation_input_tokens":10190,"cache_read_input_tokens":62195,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":10190,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":3,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"global"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c1872df7-a0d3-46d4-8ee3-4341bd508948","uuid":"63c8c203-f7f8-4816-9f13-cace8d4f887b","request_id":"req_011CcVCc98inYnNKYu1eX4Qy"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_015DYd12Xsianq4szJJQsYuQ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01AgLvsMXfffr6LcWAD3sMkf","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/workspace/.claude/tools/cost_rank","content":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"cost_rank — localize the carried-input cost across TRAIN rollouts.\n\nReads rollouts/**/metrics.json and (optionally) transcript.jsonl to rank tasks\nby total input_tokens and to show *where* the carried context balloons.\n\nUsage:\n  cost_rank                 # rank all tasks by input_tokens (one line each)\n  cost_rank <task_substr>   # per-turn breakdown for the first matching task:\n                            #   per-turn prompt size, tool results, and an\n                            #   estimate of how much \"resident raw read/bash\n                            #   output\" is being re-carried each turn.\n\nThe key cost model (verified): metrics.input_tokens == sum over turns of the\nper-turn prompt size. Context grows as docs are read and is re-sent every later\nturn, so big early reads dominate. This tool surfaces that.\n\"\"\"\nimport json, sys, glob, os\n\nROOT = os.path.join(os.path.dirname(__file__), \"..\", \"..\", \"rollouts\")\nROOT = os.path.abspath(ROOT)\n\n\ndef rank_all():\n    rows = []\n    for mp in glob.glob(os.path.join(ROOT, \"*\", \"iter0\", \"metrics.json\")):\n        task = mp.split(\"/\")[-3]\n        try:\n            m = json.load(open(mp))\n        except Exception:\n            continue\n        it = m.get(\"input_tokens\", 0)\n        ot = m.get(\"output_tokens\", 0)\n        tc = m.get(\"turn_count\", 0)\n        dr = m.get(\"documents_read\", 0)\n        # crude: input per turn ~ avg resident context; ratio in/out shows how\n        # input-bound the task is.\n        rows.append((it, ot, tc, dr, task))\n    rows.sort(reverse=True)\n    tot = sum(r[0] for r in rows)\n    print(f\"{'input_tok':>12} {'out_tok':>9} {'turns':>5} {'docs':>4} {'in/out':>6}  task\")\n    for it, ot, tc, dr, task in rows:\n        ratio = (it / ot) if ot else 0\n        print(f\"{it:>12,} {ot:>9,} {tc:>5} {dr:>4} {ratio:>6.0f}  {task[:64]}\")\n    print(f\"\\nTOTAL input_tokens across {len(rows)} tasks: {tot:,}  (mean {tot//max(1,len(rows)):,})\")\n\n\ndef breakdown(substr):\n    cand = [d for d in glob.glob(os.path.join(ROOT, \"*\", \"iter0\"))\n            if substr in d]\n    if not cand:\n        print(f\"no task dir matching '{substr}'\")\n        return\n    tdir = cand[0]\n    task = tdir.split(\"/\")[-2]\n    tpath = os.path.join(tdir, \"transcript.jsonl\")\n    print(f\"== {task} ==\")\n    # Track running estimate of resident \"raw output\" bytes (read/bash results).\n    resident_chars = 0\n    cum_in = 0\n    print(f\"{'turn':>4} {'in_tok':>9} {'cum_in':>11} {'tools':<22} {'resultlen':>10}\")\n    cur_turn = None\n    pending = []  # (name, reslen) within a turn\n    for line in open(tpath):\n        d = json.loads(line)\n        role = d.get(\"role\")\n        if role == \"assistant\":\n            it = d.get(\"input_tokens\") or 0\n            cum_in += it\n            tcs = d.get(\"tool_calls\") or []\n            names = \",\".join(t[\"name\"] for t in tcs)\n            print(f\"{d.get('turn'):>4} {it:>9,} {cum_in:>11,} {names:<22}\")\n        elif role == \"tool\":\n            rl = len(d.get(\"result\") or \"\")\n            nm = d.get(\"tool_name\", \"\")\n            if rl > 2000:\n                print(f\"{'':>4} {'':>9} {'':>11} {'  -> '+nm:<22} {rl:>10,}\")\n    print(f\"\\ntotal input_tokens (sum per turn) = {cum_in:,}\")\n\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    if len(sys.argv) > 1:\n        breakdown(sys.argv[1])\n    else:\n        rank_all()\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":160,"cache_creation_input_tokens":10190,"cache_read_input_tokens":62195,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":10190,"epheme