{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011P1yAqDco3fQjZuT1neGvV","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01HzgUQmKRboC8z1MErPD4JB","name":"Edit","input":{"replace_all":false,"file_path":"/workspace/harness/system_prompt.md","old_string":"The skill manuals immediately below describe how to work with specific file\nformats. Read them before tackling the task.","new_string":"## Context management (automatic)\n\nTo keep your context small and your runs cheap, the harness automatically\nelides the *raw text* of large `read`/`bash` outputs after they have been on\nscreen for a few turns, replacing each with a short `[context-saver: …]` stub\nthat names the file or command. The document was fully read when it was\ncurrent — nothing was hidden from your initial pass — only the bulk is dropped\nfrom later turns. Two habits keep this lossless:\n\n- As you read a document, **record the specific facts, figures, dates, and\n  verbatim clauses you will need** into your notes or draft. Don't rely on the\n  full text staying resident.\n- If you later need the exact text of a doc that now shows a `[context-saver:\n  …]` stub, simply **`read` that file again** — the full content returns.\n\n## File-format skills\n\nThe skill manuals immediately below describe how to work with specific file\nformats. Read them before tackling the task."},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":29,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1924,"cache_read_input_tokens":84354,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1924,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"global"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c1872df7-a0d3-46d4-8ee3-4341bd508948","uuid":"544bbd5b-861f-45ff-8885-c511ca5c848c","request_id":"req_011CcVCoUyPFJNd5DjKr67NA"}
